<definition xml:id="definition-EM" acro="EM">
    <title>Eigenspace of a Matrix</title>
    <idx>eigenspace</idx>
    <statement>
        <p>Suppose that <m>A</m> is a square matrix and <m>\lambda</m> is an eigenvalue of <m>A</m>.  Then the <term>eigenspace</term> of <m>A</m> for <m>\lambda</m>, <m>\eigenspace{A}{\lambda}</m>, is the set of all the eigenvectors of <m>A</m> for <m>\lambda</m>, together with the inclusion of the zero vector.</p>
    </statement>
</definition>
